text: Yoshihisa Yoshikawa (吉川 貴久, September 4, 1936 – October 12, 2019) was a Japanese shooter. He competed at the 1960, 1964, 1968 and 1972 Olympics in the 50 m pistol event. He won bronze medals in 1960 and 1964. ==References== Category:1936 births Category:2019 deaths Category:Deaths from heart failure Category:Olympic bronze medalists for Japan Category:Sport shooters
